<p><sup id="cite_ref-32" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-32"><span>[</span>32<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-33" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33"><span>[</span>33<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The largest denominations by number of adherents according to the <a href="/wiki/Canada_2001_Census" title="Canada 2001 Census">2001 census</a> were none (atheist, agnostic, and so on.) with 1,388,300 (35.9%); <a href="/wiki/Protestant" title="Protestant" class="mw-redirect">Protestant</a> with 1,213,295 (31.4%); the <a href="/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Church" title="Roman Catholic Church" class="mw-redirect">Roman Catholic Church</a> with 675,320 (17%); the <a href="/wiki/United_Church_of_Canada" title="United Church of Canada">United Church of Canada</a> with 361,840 (9%); and the <a href="/wiki/Anglican_Church_of_Canada" title="Anglican Church of Canada">Anglican Church of Canada</a> with 298,375 (8%).<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34"><span>[</span>34<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
